02:25:47,361 --> 02:25:52,298
Benjamin Button,
this is my husband, Robert.

1677
02:25:52,399 --> 02:25:54,799
- How do you do?
- A pleasure.

1678
02:26:02,943 --> 02:26:05,935
Well, it was very nice to meet you.

1679
02:26:06,046 --> 02:26:07,843
- We'll be in the car, darling.
- All right.

1680
02:26:07,948 --> 02:26:09,074
Bye.

1681
02:26:09,817 --> 02:26:11,580
I'm just locking up.

1682
02:26:16,356 --> 02:26:17,414
Wow.

1683
02:26:19,960 --> 02:26:22,827
She's beautiful. Like her mother.

1684
02:26:24,431 --> 02:26:26,899
- Does she dance?
- Not very well.

1685
02:26:27,000 --> 02:26:28,900
I guess that'd be
from my side of things.

1686
02:26:29,002 --> 02:26:30,993
She's a dear, sweet girl.

1687
02:26:32,206 --> 02:26:36,540
She seems a little lost.
But then, who isn't at 12?

1688
02:26:36,744 --> 02:26:40,976
A lot of her reminds me of you.

1689
02:26:41,882 --> 02:26:45,818
My husband, he's a widower, or was...
Was a widower.

1690
02:26:46,220 --> 02:26:50,122
He's an incredibly kind, just bright,
adventurous man.

1691
02:26:53,293 --> 02:26:55,989
- He's been a terrific father.
- Good.

1692
02:27:00,701 --> 02:27:04,603
- You are so much younger.
- Only on the outside.

1693
02:27:06,707 --> 02:27:08,231
You were right.

1694
02:27:10,010 --> 02:27:13,377
I couldn't have been raising both of you.

1695
02:27:13,480 --> 02:27:15,243
I'm not that strong.

1696
02:27:19,453 --> 02:27:21,478
So, where are you staying?

1697
02:27:24,158 --> 02:27:25,147
What are you gonna do?

1698
02:27:25,259 --> 02:27:29,059
I'm staying at the Pontchartrain Hotel
on the Avenue.

1699
02:27:29,163 --> 02:27:32,690
I don't know what I'm gonna do.

1700
02:27:32,800 --> 02:27:33,960
But...

1701
02:27:40,474 --> 02:27:42,101
They're waiting.

1702
02:28:24,251 --> 02:28:27,516
I remember that. That was him?

1703
02:28:30,190 --> 02:28:31,350
The hurricane has changed directions.

1704
02:28:31,458 --> 02:28:33,289
It's going to make landfall
sometime soon.

1705
02:28:33,393 --> 02:28:35,122
- Am I supposed to do something?
- Arrangements are being made

1706
02:28:35,229 --> 02:28:36,457
to move people, but it's up to you.

1707
02:28:36,563 --> 02:28:38,428
No. No, we're... We're staying.

1708
02:28:38,532 --> 02:28:41,160
I'll let you know if anything changes.

1709
02:28:43,203 --> 02:28:47,537
"That night, while I was sitting
and wondering why I came back at all,

1710
02:28:47,641 --> 02:28:49,973
"there was a knock at the door. "

1711
02:28:53,614 --> 02:28:54,842
Come in.

1712
02:29:09,162 --> 02:29:10,823
Are you all right?

1713
02:29:13,934 --> 02:29:18,030
I'm sorry,
I don't know what I'm doing here.

1714
02:29:27,080 --> 02:29:28,570
Nothing lasts.

1715
02:29:32,052 --> 02:29:34,384
I have never stopped loving you.

1716
02:29:40,394 --> 02:29:43,090
Oh, but, Benjamin,
I'm an old woman now.

1717
02:29:53,740 --> 02:29:55,935
Some things you never forget.

1718
02:30:16,229 --> 02:30:17,287
<i>...so few people even know</i>

1719
02:30:17,397 --> 02:30:19,092
<i>that you were ever in jail
in the first place.</i>

1720
02:30:19,199 --> 02:30:21,394
<i>I'll tell you, I am sick about it, too,</i>

1721
02:30:21,501 --> 02:30:24,061
<i>because, please,
if they're not gonna give you an award</i>

1722
02:30:24,171 --> 02:30:26,230
<i>like "Man of the Year,"
at least what they could do</i>

1723
02:30:26,340 --> 02:30:29,002
<i>is stop having you listed
as an ex-convict</i>

1724
02:30:29,109 --> 02:30:31,600
<i>which I think is, again, so unfair.</i>

1725
02:30:44,391 --> 02:30:46,188
Good night, Benjamin.

1726
02:30:47,728 --> 02:30:49,389
Good night, Daisy.

1727
02:30:52,599 --> 02:30:56,831
<i>And as I knew I would,
I watched her go.</i>

1728
02:30:59,573 --> 02:31:01,871
That's the last thing he wrote.

1729
02:31:03,043 --> 02:31:07,605
Sometime after your father passed,

1730
02:31:07,714 --> 02:31:10,547
there was a call.

1731
02:31:13,620 --> 02:31:14,780
Hello.

1732
02:31:15,889 --> 02:31:17,379
Yes, speaking.

1733
02:31:20,727 --> 02:31:23,218
I'm sorry, I don't understand.

1734
02:31:33,073 --> 02:31:34,938
It's the corner house.

1735
02:31:57,130 --> 02:31:58,495
Come on in.

1736
02:32:04,104 --> 02:32:06,129
- I'm Daisy Fuller.
- I'm David Hernandez,

1737
02:32:06,239 --> 02:32:09,936
with the Orleans Parish Department
of Child Welfare Services.

1738
02:32:10,043 --> 02:32:12,671
He was living in a condemned building.

1739
02:32:14,481 --> 02:32:16,779
The police found this with him.

1740
02:32:16,883 --> 02:32:19,818
This address.
It's got your name in it a lot.

1741
02:32:21,021 --> 02:32:23,649
He's in very poor health.
He was taken to the hospital.

1742
02:32:23,757 --> 02:32:27,784
He doesn't seem to know who
or where he is. He's very confused.

1743
02:32:27,894 --> 02:32:31,455
I was telling Mr. Hernandez
that Benjamin is one of us.

1744
02:32:31,565 --> 02:32:35,399
If he needs a place to stay,
it's all right, he can stay here.

1745
02:33:04,865 --> 02:33:06,127
Benjamin?

1746
02:33:10,003 --> 02:33:11,800
You play beautifully.

1747
02:33:15,308 --> 02:33:17,139
He doesn't seem to like to be touched.

1748
02:33:17,244 --> 02:33:18,905
He goes in and out
of states of recognition.

1749
02:33:19,012 --> 02:33:20,639
The doctors say,
if they didn't know any better,

1750
02:33:20,747 --> 02:33:23,181
he has the beginnings of dementia.

1751
02:33:24,985 --> 02:33:26,714
Do you remember me?

1752
02:33:29,890 --> 02:33:31,221
I'm Daisy.

1753
02:33:33,827 --> 02:33:35,294
I'm Benjamin.

1754
02:33:41,001 --> 02:33:43,663
It's nice to meet you, Benjamin.

1755
02:33:45,372 --> 02:33:50,742
Would you mind if I sit with you?
I would love to hear you play.

1756
02:33:54,614 --> 02:33:56,104
Do I know you?

1757
02:34:01,087 --> 02:34:02,714
<i>- I want some breakfast.
- And every day,</i>

1758
02:34:02,822 --> 02:34:06,781
<i>I would stop by to make sure
that he was comfortable.</i>

1759
02:34:06,893 --> 02:34:09,521
- No, I didn't.
- You just finished eating.

1760
02:34:09,629 --> 02:34:11,961
Don't think I don't know
what you're doing!

1761
02:34:12,065 --> 02:34:14,795
You're all fucking liars!

1762
02:34:14,901 --> 02:34:17,826
He doesn't believe
he just had his breakfast.

1763
02:34:19,139 --> 02:34:22,768
Now, why don't we see

1764
02:34:22,876 --> 02:34:26,243
if we can't find something else
for you to do?

1765
02:34:26,413 --> 02:34:29,576
I have a feeling
there's a lot of things I can't remember.

1766
02:34:29,683 --> 02:34:31,583
Well, like what, sugar?

1767
02:34:32,852 --> 02:34:36,845
It's like there's this whole life I had,

1768
02:34:38,325 --> 02:34:40,725
and I can't remember what it was.

1769
02:34:43,530 --> 02:34:44,861
It's okay.

1770
02:34:46,967 --> 02:34:48,434
It's okay to forget things.

1771
02:34:48,668 --> 02:34:54,231
<i>Many times, he would simply forget
who or where he was.</i>

1772
02:34:54,574 --> 02:34:56,235
There he is, he's up there on the roof.

1773
02:34:56,343 --> 02:34:58,038
<i>It wasn't easy.</i>

1774
02:34:58,144 --> 02:35:00,374
- Benjamin!
- I can see everything!

1775
02:35:00,480 --> 02:35:02,243
- I can see the big river!
- That's right,

1776
02:35:02,349 --> 02:35:04,078
you can see everything, sweetheart.

1777
02:35:04,184 --> 02:35:06,175
I can see the graveyard
where Mama's buried,

1778
02:35:06,286 --> 02:35:09,653
- and all those other people.
- I want you to come down!

1779
02:35:09,756 --> 02:35:13,487
- What if I could fly?
- I knew a man who could fly.

1780
02:35:14,494 --> 02:35:17,463
You come down
and I'll tell you all about him.

1781
02:35:21,034 --> 02:35:22,626
Somebody go up there.

1782
02:35:29,242 --> 02:35:32,211
<i>He was five when I moved in.</i>

1783
02:35:32,312 --> 02:35:36,772
<i>Nearly the same age I was
when I had met him.</i>

1784
02:35:42,789 --> 02:35:46,725
"This is the picture
of Old Man Kangaroo

1785
02:35:46,826 --> 02:35:49,260
"at 5:00 in the afternoon

1786
02:35:49,362 --> 02:35:52,820
"when he had got
his beautiful hind legs. "

1787
02:35:54,067 --> 02:35:55,364
<i>The days passed.</i>

1788
02:35:55,468 --> 02:35:59,700
<i>And I watched as he forgot how to walk</i>

1789
02:36:04,944 --> 02:36:07,378
<i>- and how to talk.
- What's my name?</i>

1790
02:36:07,847 --> 02:36:09,178
I'm Daisy.

1791
02:36:10,350 --> 02:36:12,113
Can you say "Daisy"?

1792
02:36:13,687 --> 02:36:18,954
<i>In 2002, they put up a new clock
in that train station.</i>

1793
02:36:25,799 --> 02:36:29,565
<i>And in the spring of 2003,</i>

1794
02:36:33,940 --> 02:36:35,601
<i>he looked at me</i>

1795
02:36:38,111 --> 02:36:43,174
<i>and I knew that he knew who I was.</i>

1796
02:36:46,720 --> 02:36:52,522
<i>And then he closed his eyes
as if to go to sleep.</i>

1797
02:37:25,091 --> 02:37:29,255
- I wish I'd known him.
- Now you do.

1798
02:37:33,767 --> 02:37:37,533
Mom, I think I should go see
what's going on.

1799
02:37:44,577 --> 02:37:46,602
Good night, Benjamin.

1800
02:38:09,002 --> 02:38:11,368
<i>We're expecting flash flooding
after the levee break.</i>

1801
02:38:11,471 --> 02:38:13,701
<i>It occurred in the Ninth Ward.</i>

1802
02:38:16,743 --> 02:38:19,576
<i>Some people are born to sit by a river.</i>

1803
02:38:21,114 --> 02:38:23,048
<i>Some get struck by lightning.</i>

1804
02:38:24,951 --> 02:38:27,044
<i>Some have an ear for music.</i>

1805
02:38:28,655 --> 02:38:30,282
<i>Some are artists.</i>

1806
02:38:31,624 --> 02:38:32,955
<i>Some swim.</i>

1807
02:38:34,394 --> 02:38:36,021
<i>Some know buttons.</i>

1808
02:38:37,831 --> 02:38:39,196
<i>Some know Shakespeare.</i>

1809
02:38:40,366 --> 02:38:42,129
<i>Some are mothers.</i>

1810
02:38:44,103 --> 02:38:47,129
<i>And some people dance.</i>